HEADWORD: Exosculate
<hw>Ex*os"cu*late</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>exosculatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>exosculari</ets> to kiss. See
<er>Osculate</er>.]</ety> <def>To kiss; especially, to kiss repeatedly
or fondly.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

